Text: It's been a long two weeks, but Anthony is finally HOME!  We are so grateful for our family and friends for their prayers, support, love, and friendship! 💚💚💚💚
Thank you! Your prayers worked! Anthony came home today! We're so grateful for all of your support!!

Please say a prayer for Anthony. Last Wednesday he was admitted to Memorial Hospital with afib. He also has fluid around his heart. This dreaded kidney disease has taken it's toll in Anthony. I pray God will make him well.
Just talked with doc. Surgery went well, but because of the blood thinners he is on she had a hard time clotting. He's doing ok, just tired and hungry. Thank you for your prayers and support!

Here she is, the third generation. We''re so proud of her!. We believe in Notre Dame. It''s not perfect, but it gets better every day. It''s better now than it was in 1955 when my Dad graduated. It''s better than it was in 1990 when we graduated. One thing hasn''t changed. It''s continuing to produce generations of people (including so many dear to me from the class of 1990) who make the world better and who are formed by our unique mission: to be a place where learning becomes service to justice.

Amazing news.....surgery was a huge success!!  The tumor we thought was attached to her colon was actually on her right ovary. That got taken outta there...5lbs out of her belly. Cut a section of her colon out that had cancer, but no bag was needed. She did great!!! Thank you all so much for the prayers and kind words. God truely is looking over her!

We could really use the power of prayer today for surgery to go well for Brian's mom. It's scary for all of us. I am sure things will go just fine but cancer is so unpredictable. We love you momma...u got this!
Just went back for surgery. Min of 2 hours is what we were told...will keep ya'll posted.

They took momma to the Critical Care Unit at 2 a.m. this morning. She isn't doing very well at this point. Unable to keep her blood pressure steady. Cancer won this battle and her body is giving up. Doctor's say she won't make it through the day. We are making sure she is very comfortable and in no more pain. Lots of tears but happy she is able to go home with her parents soon. God will be getting another angel. We love you so much Teresa Stark. You have put up one hell of a fight and we are so proud of you.
I have to say that I have some of the most amazing friends!! Bringing us dinner, helping with funeral arrangements, and just being there for us. Thank you all so much!!!
You all are incredibly kind. Thank you for all of your support. She is still hanging in there right now. She is a tough one for sure. We will keep everyone posted.

Promises.  In the last (almost) 11 YEARS I have been either pregnant or breastfeeding for 8.5 of them.  8.5 YEARS of nourishing not only my body but another humans.  And let’s be honest it is great, but all good things come to an end am I right?? 😉. Taking care of myself and being active has always been on the to-do list but not quite a priority.  A week ago I made a promise to myself to take care of me.  . Each day I hit my steps, workout, and sweat because I have promised myself.  If we don’t keep promises to ourselves then how can we to others?. This mama is done pouring from an empty cup. What are doing for yourself to fill your cup?. #pregnancy #breastfeeding #fourbabies #losethebabyweight #iamher
